    "Physicians rely on their extensive medical knowledge and scientific grounding to make assessments, whereas AI systems rely on different features to classify medical images or data.",
    "67 Another way of putting it is that humans and AI are complementary.",
    "See the discussion on humanmachine interaction in Sect. 4.4.",
    "68 See, for example, the policy paper on self-driving cars by the UK Centre for Data Ethics and Innovation, in which the authors suggest that it might not be enough for AI to be as safe as other products but that AI actually must be safer as there is a lower tolerance for mistakes [Centre for Data Ethics and Innovation.",
    "Responsible Innovation in Self-Driving Vehicles. https:// www."
